betterquesting:10.desc:8: Plates are an important part of the economy, you need 'em, and so does everyone else. You can sell any surplus plates you've got if you would like to make some money.
Get wood.
If the pack updates, or the quests break somehow, use this quest to fix it

Meat is filling and all, but you are going to quickly run out of animals, they don't breed like they used to.

Make some crop sticks to start using agricraft to make better seeds for food.

Mobs don't spawn in the overworld, so you don't have to be too careful about protecting your things, however you are probably going to want to sleep the night away.

Craft a bed to get some things to start off your journey.

You may or may not have noticed that some logistical solutions are much cheaper than they are normally.

Craft a hopper to unlock the progression quest line.

You may have realized that charcoal and coal aren't what they used to be, if you want better fuel, you are going to need a coke oven.

A coke oven is a 3x3x3 solid cube of coke bricks, right click the center-front block with an Engineer's Hammer to activate it.

You'll find that the coke oven is useful for other things as well.
You're going to need energy, lots of it.
You aren't going to want to use basic tools, here's everything you need to make advanced Tinker's Construct tools.

You are going to need a higher tech solution to the Forge Hammer.

That's where the Compactor comes in, it can do everything the Forge Hammer can do, and more.

Creosote is useful as both a fuel and for use in treated wood.

Which is good reason for many to buy it in bulk.

Once your quarry reaches bedrock, you may find some bedrock ores which contain thousands of ores.

Craft a Bedrock Miner to mine these ores.

No Description
Data transfer is an important part of any factory.
A simple, but essential piece to almost all industrial machines.

With no mobs, you may be asking "What do I need armor for?"

I assure you, you'll find out.
Combine this with one of your darksteel armor pieces to upgrade the damage resistance.
Use these the same way you used the basic capacitors to further upgrade your damage resistance.
Max out your damage resistance with these capacitors
You may find your armor running out of energy, combine your helmet with this solar panel to upgrade it's energy production.

Still running out of energy?

This should aleviate that.
You can either attatch a glider, similar to the gliders from mods of old or you may choose the elytra.

Not enough space.

When you open your inventory, you should notice slots for memory cards, place the memory card you recieved from this quest in the first slot.
In case the extra inventory space wasn't quite enough, here's a whole lot more.

You have a handy bag, but you may want a way to interface your memory cards with the world.

That's where these come in.
In case the regular handy chest just wasn't large enough.
They just get bigger and bigger.
Like, a lot bigger.

Not enough (digital) space.

You can have up to four separate memory cards in your handy bag or chest.
You may find that you are filling up your memory cards, don't worry, you can increase the stack sizes inside your cards.

Where it all begins.

Unlock other questing sections from here, as well as learn the basics for the pack.
Intended progression through mods.

Earn money by selling a multitude of resources.

Use all that money you've earned to buy some cool things.
You've already got quite a few machines, now's time to make some more.
You are probably running out of resources pretty quickly, you should probably fix that.
The decimation of the world around you requires you to move on.
Exchange Science Packs to unlock new technologies
